<p class="head">Mississourie <span class="AddHand-author">Continued</span> or rather Supplement to his</p>
<p></p>
<p class="head"><span class="DelHand-author">third Journey</span> <span class="AddHand-author">2</span><span class="AddHand-author"><sup>nd</sup></span><span class="AddHand-author"> Journey</span></p>
<p><span class="fw" style="text-decoration:underline;">1805</span>
</p>
<p>July 10<sup>th</sup></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">To celebrate a great festival all the old men of the Enasas village assembled at the lodge of the first chief &#8211; in order to appoint proper officers to Keep the peace during its duration<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">11<sup>th</sup></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">This morning at <span class="DelHand-author">the</span> break of day an old man harangued through the village. Soon after <span class="AddHand-author">appeared</span> twelve robust Young men with their heads <span class="DelHand-author">enclossed</span> in bladders and their bodies <span class="DelHand-author">bare</span> <span class="AddHand-author">bare</span> <span class="DelHand-author">appeared<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  The half of their bodies downwards to the heels were</span> painted <span class="AddHand-author">half</span> in vermil<span class="DelHand-author">l</span>ion &#8211; <span class="DelHand-author">The other half were painted with</span> <span class="AddHand-author">&amp; half with</span> white earth &#8211; <span class="DelHand-author">denoting <span class="AddHand-author">as</span> the</span> <span class="AddHand-author">as</span> emblems of punishment and pardon united in the same persons<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="DelHand-author">appeared</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">These guardians <span class="DelHand-author">entered</span> of <span class="AddHand-author">this Noble</span> Order entered every lodge <span class="DelHand-author">and directed the women to <span class="AddHand-author">attend their duty as</span> go into the woods for branches to cover the Medicine Lodge</span> <span class="AddHand-author">giving directions</span>.  <span class="DelHand-author"><span class="AddHand-author">When</span> this Lodge whose <span class="DelHand-author"><span class="AddHand-author">sp</span><span class="Gap">[&#8230;]</span></span> frame is always standing in the field at some distance from the village &#8211; and supported upon a pillar, which rises in the center, <span class="DelHand-author">of</span> twenty five feet high.  When this Lodge was ready</span> <span class="AddHand-author">A lodge </span><span class="DelHand-author"><span class="AddHand-author">the Medicine Lodge</span></span><span class="AddHand-author"> was prepared</span><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  The Men with their pipes and Drums <span class="DelHand-author">walked into it</span> <span class="DelHand-author"><span class="AddHand-author">at first</span></span> <span class="AddHand-author">entered</span> &#8211; the women followed <span class="DelHand-author">them</span> with an assortment of the best <span class="AddHand-author">of eatables </span><span class="DelHand-author">things that could be found</span> for <span class="DelHand-author">the feast</span><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="DelHand-author">Every</span> <span class="AddHand-author">The</span> Dishes were aired over a fire at the Door <span class="DelHand-author">of the lodge made for the purpose</span> and <span class="DelHand-author">out of which <span class="Gap">[&#8230;]</span></span> an offering <span class="AddHand-author">out of each </span>was made to the Sun <span class="DelHand-author">which <span class="Gap">[&#8230;]</span> were left for the Dogs</span> <span class="DelHand-author"><span class="AddHand-author">to eat</span></span>  When <span class="DelHand-author">the eating business <span class="Gap">[&#8230;]</span></span> <span class="AddHand-author">When dinner</span> was over &#8211; all <span class="DelHand-author">hands</span> Smo<span class="DelHand-author">a</span>ked and danced for the rest of the <span class="DelHand-author">day</span> Evening<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p>12<sup>th</sup></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">This afternoon several Young men placed themselves extended upon their bellies.  Then an old man with the <span class="DelHand-author">beard</span> <span class="AddHand-author">barb</span> of an arrow</p>
<p style="text-align:right;">bore</p>

